@flint v0 hybrid
@cb[
  μ1=auth.middleware;
  μ2=expiry_cmp;
  κ1=skew_budget_30s;
  κ2=no_wider_accept;
  ρ1=boundary_eq;
  τ1=refresh_loop_401
]

G: fix(μ2) ∧ encode(κ1)
C: κ1 ∧ κ2 ∧ minimal_diff
H: cmp(expMs<nowMs) ∧ refresh_uses(expMs<=nowMs-30000) ⇒ τ1 @ ρ1
P: normalize(expMs,ms) → Δ(reject iff nowMs>expMs+30000) → align(refresh_rule) → single_site(μ2)
V: unit(nowMs==expMs+30000→accept) ∧ unit(nowMs==expMs+30001→401) ∧ unit(nowMs<=expMs→accept) ∧ unit(missing_token→401) ∧ unit(malformed→401) ∧ unit(unit_mismatch_sec_vs_ms→401)
R: ! widen_skew_beyond_30s ∧ ! drift_between_reject_and_refresh
Q: refresh_path_shares_same_helper ?
A: patch(μ2): reject ⇔ nowMs > expMs + 30000 ∧ reuse_in(refresh)

[AUDIT]
bug: reject uses strict `<` while skew budget 30s not encoded, so boundary at exact exp

@flint v0 hybrid

G: refactor(loadUser) → async_await
C: preserve(order) ∧ single_error_map(next(err)) ∧ min_diff
P:
  step1: validate(req.params.id) ∨ missing_id → next(err)
  step2: user = await db.findUser(id)
  step3: if !user → next(err)
  step4: await audit.log(user)
  step5: await cache.set(user)
  step6: res / next()
V:
  test(success_path) ∧
  test(missing_id_early_fail) ∧
  test(db.findUser_reject → next(err)) ∧
  test(not_found → next(err)) ∧
  test(no_double_next)
R:
  ! this_binding(db.findUser) → wrap_if_needed
  ! db.findUser_not_promise → util.promisify
  ! audit/cache_reject → route(next(err)) not swallow
A:
```js
async function loadUser(req, res, next) {
  try {
    const { id } = req.params;
    if (!id) return next(new Error("missing_id"));

    const user = await db.findUser(id);
    if (!user) return next(new Error("not_found"));

    await audit.log(user);
    await cache.set(user);

    req.user = user;
    next();
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
}
```

[AUDIT]
keep order: validate → load → not_found → audit → cache → respond.
single error path stays next(err) via try/catch.
if db.findUser is callback-style or bound to this, wrap

